Moving to online classes brings its own difficulties, too, as some subjects typically require in-person, hands-on elements that don't translate well to video.
Students in favor of this grading option say it helps ensure they learn the required material sufficiently without adding in the pressure of letter grades.
In Florida, three large state universities announced March 24 that they would switch to pass/fail grading in response to student petitions.
The University of Wisconsin-Madison declared March 26 that the "unprecedented situation" called for a pass/fail grading option.
Some colleges have made small concessions: The University of Arizona is allowing students to request pass/fail grading from professors.